‐ Kirito: WELL...

98
00:04:55,462 --> 00:04:57,923
IF WE SEE EACH OTHER
EVERY DAY FOR A YEAR, IT'S‐‐

99
00:04:57,964 --> 00:04:59,716
Asuna: STOP. THAT WAS
A RHETORICAL QUESTION,

100
00:04:59,758 --> 00:05:01,384
SMARTY‐PANTS. COME ON.

101
00:05:01,426 --> 00:05:03,220
Kirito: OKAY, OKAY.

102
00:05:05,847 --> 00:05:07,307
I DON'T KNOW ABOUT YOU,

103
00:05:07,349 --> 00:05:09,559
BUT I THINK THE IMPERIAL PALACE
IS INTERESTING.

104
00:05:09,601 --> 00:05:13,104
Asuna: INTERESTING?
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

105
00:05:13,146 --> 00:05:15,398
Kirito: IT'S TWO KILOMETERS
NORTH TO SOUTH,

106
00:05:15,440 --> 00:05:17,150
1.5 EAST TO WEST,

107
00:05:17,192 --> 00:05:19,444
AND IT TAKES UP
20% OF CHIYODA WARD.

108
00:05:19,486 --> 00:05:21,780
THERE AREN'T ANY SUBWAYS
OR TUNNELS UNDER IT,

109
00:05:21,822 --> 00:05:23,532
AND IT'S A NO‐FLY ZONE.

110
00:05:23,573 --> 00:05:25,826
IT'S KINDA COOL,
DON'T YOU THINK?

111
00:05:25,867 --> 00:05:27,410
I MEAN, IT'S THIS
BIG RESTRICTED AREA

112
00:05:27,452 --> 00:05:29,496
RIGHT IN THE MIDDLE OF TOKYO.

113
00:05:29,538 --> 00:05:32,374
NOT ONLY IS IT CUT OFF
FROM EVERYTHING PHYSICALLY,

114
00:05:32,415 --> 00:05:34,251
BUT INFORMATION‐WISE AS WELL.

115
00:05:34,292 --> 00:05:35,418
SEE THAT?

116
00:05:35,460 --> 00:05:37,504
IT'S A SURVEILLANCE CAMERA.

117
00:05:37,546 --> 00:05:40,632
THIS PLACE WAS SET UP WITH
ITS VERY OWN CLOSED NETWORK.

118
00:05:40,674 --> 00:05:42,843
YOU CAN'T EVEN ACCESS IT
FROM THE OUTSIDE.

119
00:05:42,884 --> 00:05:45,929
Asuna: WOW.
THAT'S A WEIRD‐LOOKING CAMERA.

120
00:05:45,971 --> 00:05:47,222
Kirito: YEAH.

121
00:05:47,264 --> 00:05:49,683
NOT ONLY IS THIS PLACE
THE HEART OF TOKYO,

122
00:05:49,724 --> 00:05:52,018
BUT IT'S ALSO
AN ISOLATED WORLD OF ITS OWN.

123
00:05:52,060 --> 00:05:54,646
MAYBE I'M EXAGGERATING
ITS COOL FACTOR.

124
00:05:54,688 --> 00:05:56,690
‐ I GET LIKE THAT.
‐ Asuna: (GIGGLES) YOU THINK?

125
00:06:02,946 --> 00:06:04,197
WOW!

126
00:06:04,239 --> 00:06:06,867
Kirito: THIS USED TO BE
THE INNER CITADEL.

127
00:06:06,908 --> 00:06:08,410
Asuna: COME ON! LET'S GO!

128
00:06:12,372 --> 00:06:14,958
(NO AUDIBLE DIALOGUE)

129
00:06:26,011 --> 00:06:28,138
Asuna: HEY, YOU KNOW
THAT QUESTIONNAIRE

130
00:06:28,179 --> 00:06:30,765
THEY GAVE US TO FILL OUT,
THE ONE ABOUT OUR FUTURE PLANS?

131
00:06:30,807 --> 00:06:32,559
DO YOU KNOW WHAT YOU
WANT TO DO YET?

132
00:06:32,601 --> 00:06:33,685
Kirito: HMM.

133
00:06:33,727 --> 00:06:35,562
I GUESS, IF ANYTHING,

134
00:06:35,604 --> 00:06:37,939
I WANNA GO FROM PLAYING GAMES
TO BEING A CREATOR.

135
00:06:37,981 --> 00:06:39,608
Asuna: A CREATOR?

136
00:06:39,649 --> 00:06:40,817
WHAT, FOR GAMES?

137
00:06:40,859 --> 00:06:42,444
Kirito: NO, NOT FOR GAMES.

138
00:06:42,485 --> 00:06:43,862
I WANNA MAKE
A HUMAN‐MACHINE INTERFACE

139
00:06:43,904 --> 00:06:46,698
TO REPLACE THE FULL‐DIVE TECH
WE USE NOW.

140
00:06:46,740 --> 00:06:48,199
I'VE BEEN GOIN'
TO ALL THESE TECH FORUMS

141
00:06:48,241 --> 00:06:49,784
TO LEARN MORE ABOUT IT,

142
00:06:49,826 --> 00:06:52,621
BUT IT'S A HECK OF A LOT
OF INFORMATION TO ABSORB.

143
00:06:54,331 --> 00:06:57,667
Asuna: AFTER I GRADUATE,
ALL I WANT IS TO BE WITH YOU.

144
00:06:57,709 --> 00:06:59,502
‐ Kirito: HUH?
‐ Asuna: I‐I MEAN...

145
00:06:59,544 --> 00:07:00,920
I‐I WISH WE COULD
FIGURE OUT A WAY

146
00:07:00,962 --> 00:07:03,131
TO LIVE WITH YUI
IN THIS WORLD, TOO!

147
00:07:03,173 --> 00:07:05,258
Kirito: WE'LL BE ABLE
TO LIVE WITH HER SOMEDAY,

148
00:07:05,300 --> 00:07:06,593
AS SOON AS WE FIGURE OUT

149
00:07:06,635 --> 00:07:08,762
HOW TO ACCESS AUGMENTED REALITY
AT WILL.

150
00:07:08,803 --> 00:07:10,055
THE ONLY THING
STANDING IN THE WAY

151
00:07:10,096 --> 00:07:11,890
IS THE DIFFERENCE
IN THE AMOUNT OF DATA.

152
00:07:11,931 --> 00:07:15,018
Asuna: DIDN'T YOU SAY SOMETHING
LIKE THAT A LITTLE WHILE AGO,

153
00:07:15,060 --> 00:07:16,436
THAT THE DIFFERENCE
BETWEEN OUR WORLD

154
00:07:16,478 --> 00:07:18,980
AND THE VIRTUAL
WAS THE AMOUNT OF DATA?

155
00:07:19,022 --> 00:07:20,649
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN, ANYWAY?

156
00:07:20,690 --> 00:07:22,942
Kirito: LET'S SEE.
IT'S LIKE THIS.

157
00:07:22,984 --> 00:07:25,403
IF WE WERE HOLDING HANDS
IN "A. L. O.,"

158
00:07:25,445 --> 00:07:28,657
IT WOULDN'T BE THE SAME
AS IN THE REAL WORLD, WOULD IT?

159
00:07:28,698 --> 00:07:30,325
Asuna: NO, IT WOULDN'T.

160
00:07:30,367 --> 00:07:34,245
YOU CAN FEEL A LOT MORE
TOUCHING A REAL HAND.

161
00:07:34,287 --> 00:07:35,497
HEY, IS THAT WHAT YOU MEAN

162
00:07:35,538 --> 00:07:37,082
BY THE DIFFERENCE
IN THE AMOUNT OF DATA?

163
00:07:37,123 --> 00:07:39,751
Kirito: YUP. AND CAN YOU IMAGINE
WHAT IT WOULD BE LIKE

164
00:07:39,793 --> 00:07:42,462
IF WE COULD REPRODUCE
THE FEEL OF SKIN AND A PULSE?

165
00:07:42,504 --> 00:07:44,005
WOULD WE BE ABLE
TO TELL THE DIFFERENCE

166
00:07:44,047 --> 00:07:46,675
BETWEEN A REAL HAND
AND AN AVATAR'S HAND?

167
00:07:46,716 --> 00:07:50,011
Asuna: I KNOW I COULD
IF I WAS TOUCHING YOUR HAND.

168
00:07:51,262 --> 00:07:53,264
BUT IT'S NOT JUST TOUCH, IS IT?

169
00:07:53,306 --> 00:07:55,517
I MEAN, IN THE REAL WORLD,
WE GET A LOT OF INFORMATION

170
00:07:55,558 --> 00:07:57,727
FROM HOW SOMETHING SOUNDS
OR TASTES.

171
00:07:57,769 --> 00:08:00,772
EVEN IF OUR AMUSPHERE RIGS
COULD ACCESS AUGMENTED REALITY,

172
00:08:00,814 --> 00:08:02,357
WE'D STILL KNOW THE DIFFERENCE.

173
00:08:02,399 --> 00:08:05,610
Kirito: YEAH. THE SECOND
YOU SAW OR TOUCHED SOMETHING,

174
00:08:05,652 --> 00:08:07,737
YOU'D KNOW
IF IT WAS REAL OR NOT.

175
00:08:07,779 --> 00:08:09,823
BUT HOPEFULLY
SOMEONE'LL COME ALONG

176
00:08:09,864 --> 00:08:12,117
AND MAKE
A TECHNOLOGICAL BREAKTHROUGH,

177
00:08:12,158 --> 00:08:13,743
AND WHATEVER THAT IS,
IT'LL HAVE TO OUTPUT

178
00:08:13,785 --> 00:08:16,830
A TON OF SENSORY DATA
ALL THE TIME.

179
00:08:16,871 --> 00:08:18,623
Asuna: THEN WE COULD
BREAK DOWN THE WALL

180
00:08:18,665 --> 00:08:21,000
BETWEEN BOTH WORLDS
AND BE WITH YUI FOREVER.

181
00:08:21,042 --> 00:08:23,294
DO YOU THINK THAT DAY
WILL EVER COME FOR US?

182
00:08:23,336 --> 00:08:24,921
Kirito: YEAH.

183
00:08:24,963 --> 00:08:27,382
Asuna: THEN GET TO WORK
AND MAKE IT HAPPEN, 'KAY?

184
00:08:27,424 --> 00:08:28,591
Kirito: OKAY.

185
00:08:49,696 --> 00:08:51,114
